7
00:01:48,047 --> 00:01:50,526
Dr. Xu, why are you drenched?

8
00:01:50,526 --> 00:01:52,526
I'll go and get changed first.

9
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:56,540
Miss, how do I get there?

10
00:02:10,030 --> 00:02:11,599
- Wait outside. 
 - Okay.

11
00:02:11,599 --> 00:02:13,223
Thank you, Doctor!

12
00:02:13,223 --> 00:02:14,400
How is his condition?

13
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:18,038
He has a serious case of pericardial effusion. Take a look at the report.

14
00:02:18,038 --> 00:02:19,532
Look.

15
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:30,900
Team Leader, his heart rate is raising.

16
00:02:38,599 --> 00:02:40,627
His pulse is weak, and his breathing is shallow.

17
00:02:40,627 --> 00:02:42,400
Prepare for pericardiocentesis.

18
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:44,840
Pericardiocentesis is a second-level surgery. Can we perform it on our own?

19
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:46,099
Am I or are you the team leader?

20
00:02:46,099 --> 00:02:48,960
Xu Qin, you don't have the qualification to execute this procedure.

21
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:51,639
The patient might die due to pericardial tamponade.

22
00:02:51,639 --> 00:02:53,719
You're only being responsible to the patient if you don't do anything uncertain.

23
00:02:53,719 --> 00:02:55,120
How do you know if I’m certain or not?

24
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:58,545
If you do it improperly, the patient might die on the operation table.

25
00:02:58,545 --> 00:02:59,760
Have you considered the consequences?

26
00:02:59,760 --> 00:03:01,840
Can you bear the responsibility?

27
00:03:04,535 --> 00:03:06,360
I can.

28
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:07,800
With what?

29
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:10,781
With this pair of hands, he won't die.

30
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:15,599
Xu Qin, didn't I make myself clear enough?

31
00:03:15,599 --> 00:03:17,919
Department Chief Xu is already on his way. Must you take this risk?

32
00:03:17,919 --> 00:03:20,800
Dr. Yang, he is a patient of Team B. Please leave.

33
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:22,319
This isn't something you can do.

34
00:03:22,319 --> 00:03:24,680
You're fooling around with a patient's life, you know?

35
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:26,553
Please leave the room.

36
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:31,832
Team Leader.

37
00:05:43,877 --> 00:05:46,313
   

38
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:49,240
Let me clean your hands thoroughly.

39
00:05:53,839 --> 00:05:55,600
- Dr. Yang. 
 - How is she?

40
00:05:57,519 --> 00:06:00,079
Kiddo, look what I've got you.

41
00:06:00,079 --> 00:06:02,759
Dear, I bought you some cakes.

42
00:06:02,759 --> 00:06:06,060
Your father is fine now. Don't worry about him, okay?

43
00:06:07,399 --> 00:06:09,099
Has she always been like this?

44
00:06:10,470 --> 00:06:11,672
Leave her to me. You can resume your work.

45
00:06:11,672 --> 00:06:14,174
Okay. You can go ahead.

46
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,319
She's a child of a single parent.

47
00:06:22,319 --> 00:06:23,560
Her father has been taking care of her.

48
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:25,480
Now, her father is in the ICU.

49
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:27,399
That's right. Poor girl.

50
00:06:27,399 --> 00:06:32,739
This storm has caused many accidents and affected many families.

51
00:06:32,739 --> 00:06:34,719
Does she have any other relatives?

52
00:06:34,719 --> 00:06:37,120
Yes. I called her aunt just now.

53
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:39,060
She said she would pick her up soon.

54
00:06:50,287 --> 00:06:52,168
Don't be afraid.

55
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:15,920
Sha Sha, the doctors are nice, aren't they?

56
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:18,160
They bought so much food for you.

57
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:19,879
Tell me what you want...

58
00:07:19,879 --> 00:07:21,639
- Please wait. 
  - We'll go and...

59
00:07:21,639 --> 00:07:23,710
Doctor?

60
00:07:23,710 --> 00:07:24,744
Hello.

61
00:07:24,744 --> 00:07:25,879
What is this?

62
00:07:25,879 --> 00:07:27,720
This is a list of things you need to pay attention to when you get back.

63
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:30,800
I wrote down the contact number of an excellent psychiatrist too.

64
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:34,080
The child was traumatized. She might need psychological counseling.

65
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:38,959
Doctor, you're so considerate.

66
00:07:38,959 --> 00:07:40,091
Don't mention it.

67
00:07:40,091 --> 00:07:42,416
Sha Sha, hurry and thank your doctor.

68
00:07:42,416 --> 00:07:43,600
Thank you, Doctor.

69
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:45,580
Don't mention it.

70
00:07:45,580 --> 00:07:48,560
Doctor, I'll take her home first.

71
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:49,845
Okay.

72
